other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 15 mm in diameter with a fluid-filled lumen and hyperenhancement with surrounding fat stranding and a few small probably reactive nodes in the right lower quadrant measuring up to 5 mm in shortest dimension.
other_tests.changes_over_time: There is a persistent ill-defined soft tissue density in the mesentery of the left upper quadrant that has not really changed since a remote prior CT. The right lung base nodule and left lower lobe nodule are unchanged since previous examinations.
